[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6760,
        "end_time": 10453,
        "text": "How does your smartphone\nknow exactly where you are?"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 10453,
        "end_time": 13756,
        "text": "The answer lies 12,000 miles \nover your head"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 13756,
        "end_time": 18229,
        "text": "in an orbiting satellite that keeps time\nto the beat of an atomic clock"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 18229,
        "end_time": 21406,
        "text": "powered by quantum mechanics."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 21406,
        "end_time": 22436,
        "text": "Phew."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 22436,
        "end_time": 24425,
        "text": "Let&#39;s break that down."
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 24425,
        "end_time": 29121,
        "text": "First of all, why is it so important \nto know what time it is on a satellite"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 29121,
        "end_time": 32149,
        "text": "when location is what\nwe&#39;re concerned about?"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 32149,
        "end_time": 34359,
        "text": "The first thing \nyour phone needs to determine"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 34359,
        "end_time": 37696,
        "text": "is how far it is from a satellite."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 37696,
        "end_time": 40883,
        "text": "Each satellite constantly \nbroadcasts radio signals"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 40883,
        "end_time": 45762,
        "text": "that travel from space to your phone\nat the speed of light."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 45762,
        "end_time": 48562,
        "text": "Your phone records \nthe signal arrival time"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 48562,
        "end_time": 51753,
        "text": "and uses it to calculate \nthe distance to the satellite"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 51753,
        "end_time": 57717,
        "text": "using the simple formula,\ndistance = c x time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 57717,
        "end_time": 63085,
        "text": "where c is the speed of light\nand time is how long the signal traveled."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 63085,
        "end_time": 64336,
        "text": "But there&#39;s a problem."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 64336,
        "end_time": 66238,
        "text": "Light is incredibly fast."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 66238,
        "end_time": 69640,
        "text": "If we were only able to calculate \ntime to the nearest second,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 69640,
        "end_time": 72950,
        "text": "every location on Earth, and far beyond,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 72950,
        "end_time": 76102,
        "text": "would seem to be the same \ndistance from the satellite."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 76102,
        "end_time": 80375,
        "text": "So in order to calculate that distance\nto within a few dozen feet,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 80375,
        "end_time": 84168,
        "text": "we need the best clock ever invented."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 84168,
        "end_time": 87697,
        "text": "Enter atomic clocks,\nsome of which are so precise"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 87697,
        "end_time": 90563,
        "text": "that they would not gain or lose a second"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 90563,
        "end_time": 95603,
        "text": "even if they ran \nfor the next 300 million years."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 95603,
        "end_time": 98847,
        "text": "Atomic clocks work \nbecause of quantum physics."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 98847,
        "end_time": 101808,
        "text": "All clocks must have a constant frequency."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 101808,
        "end_time": 105371,
        "text": "In other words, a clock must carry out\nsome repetitive action"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 105371,
        "end_time": 109385,
        "text": "to mark off equivalent increments of time."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 109385,
        "end_time": 112731,
        "text": "Just as a grandfather clock \nrelies on the constant swinging"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 112731,
        "end_time": 115847,
        "text": "back and forth of a pendulum \nunder gravity,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 115847,
        "end_time": 117939,
        "text": "the tick tock of an atomic clock"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 117939,
        "end_time": 123041,
        "text": "is maintained by the transition \nbetween two energy levels of an atom."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 123041,
        "end_time": 126069,
        "text": "This is where quantum physics \ncomes into play."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 126069,
        "end_time": 129311,
        "text": "Quantum mechanics \nsays that atoms carry energy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 129311,
        "end_time": 133168,
        "text": "but they can&#39;t take on \njust any arbitrary amount."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 133168,
        "end_time": 138215,
        "text": "Instead, atomic energy \nis constrained to a precise set of levels."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 138215,
        "end_time": 140300,
        "text": "We call these quanta."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 140300,
        "end_time": 144402,
        "text": "As a simple analogy, \nthink about driving a car onto a freeway."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 144402,
        "end_time": 145730,
        "text": "As you increase your speed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 145730,
        "end_time": 152222,
        "text": "you would normally continuously go \nfrom, say, 20 miles\/hour up to 70 miles\/hour."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 152222,
        "end_time": 154792,
        "text": "Now, if you had a quantum atomic car,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 154792,
        "end_time": 157778,
        "text": "you wouldn&#39;t accelerate \nin a linear fashion."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 157778,
        "end_time": 164495,
        "text": "Instead, you would instantaneously jump,\nor transition, from one speed to the next."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 164495,
        "end_time": 168768,
        "text": "For an atom, when a transition \noccurs from one energy level to another,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 168768,
        "end_time": 170183,
        "text": "quantum mechanics says"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 170183,
        "end_time": 174622,
        "text": "that the energy difference \nis equal to a characteristic frequency,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 174622,
        "end_time": 177199,
        "text": "multiplied by a constant,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 177199,
        "end_time": 182815,
        "text": "where the change in energy is equal to \na number, called Planck&#39;s constant,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 182815,
        "end_time": 185092,
        "text": "times the frequency."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 185092,
        "end_time": 190297,
        "text": "That characteristic frequency \nis what we need to make our clock."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 190297,
        "end_time": 196311,
        "text": "GPS satellites rely on cesium and rubidium\natoms as frequency standards."
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 196311,
        "end_time": 198651,
        "text": "In the case of cesium 133,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 198651,
        "end_time": 208846,
        "text": "the characteristic clock frequency\nis 9,192,631,770 Hz."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 208846,
        "end_time": 211636,
        "text": "That&#39;s 9 billion cycles per second."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 211636,
        "end_time": 213625,
        "text": "That&#39;s a really fast clock."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 213625,
        "end_time": 216005,
        "text": "No matter how skilled a clockmaker may be,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 216005,
        "end_time": 218160,
        "text": "every pendulum, wind-up mechanism"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 218160,
        "end_time": 222760,
        "text": "and quartz crystal resonates \nat a slightly different frequency."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 222760,
        "end_time": 226969,
        "text": "However, every cesium 133 atom \nin the universe"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 226969,
        "end_time": 230818,
        "text": "oscillates at the same exact frequency."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 230818,
        "end_time": 233261,
        "text": "So thanks to the atomic clock,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 233261,
        "end_time": 237279,
        "text": "we get a time reading accurate\nto within 1 billionth of a second,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 237279,
        "end_time": 242294,
        "text": "and a very precise measurement\nof the distance from that satellite."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 242294,
        "end_time": 246821,
        "text": "Let&#39;s ignore the fact that you&#39;re almost\ndefinitely on Earth."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 246821,
        "end_time": 250327,
        "text": "We now know that you&#39;re at a fixed \ndistance from the satellite."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 250327,
        "end_time": 253187,
        "text": "In other words, you&#39;re somewhere \non the surface of a sphere"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 253187,
        "end_time": 255950,
        "text": "centered around the satellite."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 255950,
        "end_time": 258137,
        "text": "Measure your distance \nfrom a second satellite"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 258137,
        "end_time": 261218,
        "text": "and you get another overlapping sphere."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 261218,
        "end_time": 262186,
        "text": "Keep doing that,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 262186,
        "end_time": 263793,
        "text": "and with just four measurements,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 263793,
        "end_time": 267269,
        "text": "and a little correction \nusing Einstein&#39;s theory of relativity,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 267269,
        "end_time": 273537,
        "text": "you can pinpoint your location to exactly\none point in space."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 273537,
        "end_time": 274970,
        "text": "So that&#39;s all it takes:"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 274970,
        "end_time": 277770,
        "text": "a multibillion-dollar \nnetwork of satellites,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 277770,
        "end_time": 279817,
        "text": "oscillating cesium atoms,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 279817,
        "end_time": 281232,
        "text": "quantum mechanics,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 281232,
        "end_time": 282327,
        "text": "relativity,"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 282327,
        "end_time": 283484,
        "text": "a smartphone,"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 283484,
        "end_time": 285727,
        "text": "and you."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 285727,
        "end_time": 287109,
        "text": "No problem."
    }
]